text.__SUMMARY__: Argyrophis klemmeri, also known as Klemmer's blind snake or the Kuala Lumpur worm snake, is a species of Asian snake in the family Typhlopidae.
text.Geographic range: A. klemmeri is found in western Malaysia.
text.Etymology: The specific name, klemmeri, is in honor of German herpetologist Konrad Klemmer.
text.Further reading:
Taylor, Edward H. (1962). "New Oriental Reptiles". Univ. Kansas Sci. Bull. 43: 209-263. (Typhlops klemmeri, new species, pp. 253–254).
